comment: Gibson (CHI) firms up as he sets the screen on Sefolosha (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Horford (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Brooks' (CHI) driving shot attempt. Brooks initiates contact on the play.
Gibson (CHI) makes contact with Millsap's (ATL) body that affects his shot attempt.
Sefolosha (ATL) makes incidental contact with Butler (CHI) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Brooks (CHI) does not obtain a legal guarding position prior to making body contact with Bazemore (ATL) that affects his shot attempt.
Gibson (CHI) continues moving as he sets the screen on Teague (ATL) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Millsap (ATL) and Horford (ATL) maintain legal guarding position and cleanly block Rose's (CHI) driving shot attempt.
Brooks (CHI) makes contact with Sefolosha's (ATL) arms and affects his driving shot attempt.
Gasol (CHI) commits a take foul on Teague (ATL).
Butler (CHI) firms up as he sets the screen on Millsap (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gibson (CHI) sets the screen on Sefolosha (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Millsap (ATL) is moving toward Butler (CHI) and makes body contact on the shot attempt.
Butler (CHI) makes contact with Korver's (ATL) arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Dunleavy (CHI) commits a take foul on Teague (ATL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Rose's (CHI) field goal attempt was released prior to the clock expiring was upheld.
